    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that makes sense. but i've been hearing a lot in my seminars that people say originalism is basically just a way for judges to push their own political agendas under the guise of history. how would a scholar respond to that criticism? is it considered a legitimate legal theory or is it more of a political tool?",
