      "content": "i see. so it's supposed to be objective. but if the historical record is often interpreted differently by different people, doesn't that just make it a subjective debate? it seems like even \"objective\" scholars might just be picking and choosing history to fit a specific viewpoint. wouldn't you say that makes the whole thing inherently more political than people want to admit?",
